content:
In the 1952 Winter Olympics, the top three countries with the most medals were:

1. Norway - 16 total medals (7 gold, 3 silver, 6 bronze)
2. Finland - 11 total medals (3 gold, 4 silver, 4 bronze)
3. Sweden - 10 total medals (4 gold, 3 silver, 3 bronze)

All three countries are from the Scandinavian region and were dominant in skiing events.
